## SECTION 5 — AUDIENCE INTELLIGENCE

**Blog Gen instruction:** Every section written for this specific reader. The informational sections explain why. The tutorial sections show how, concisely.

**Who they are:**
Women 20–40, DIY-minded, trying to cut salon costs without sacrificing quality. Many have tried doing their nails at home and been frustrated — polish chips within two days, designs look amateurish, cuticles are messy, glitter is impossible to remove. They've watched TikTok hacks but don't always understand why they work or how to avoid the failure modes. Motivated by practicality and pride: they want nails that actually look good, not just theoretically achievable ones.

**What they want:**
Hacks that solve their actual problems — not a general list of nail tips they've seen before. They want to understand the mechanism ("why does this work?"), the quick execution ("what do I do?"), and the failure to avoid ("what goes wrong?"). They want confidence that they've actually chosen the right hack for their specific problem.

**What frustrates them:**
- Generic lists that recycle the same 8 hacks endlessly (ice water, base coat, toothpick)
