### APPENDIX — 73 HACKS MASTER LIST

*Blog Gen Agent uses this list to name and sequence every hack. Mechanism, method, and failure note are written from research — this list is the authoritative index.*

**H2-2: PREP HACKS (1–12)**
1. Dehydrate the nail plate with rubbing alcohol before base coat
2. Roll the polish bottle, never shake it
3. Push cuticles back with a warm washcloth, not a metal pusher
4. File in one direction only — never saw back and forth
5. Buff ridges with a 4-way buffer but only once a month
6. Soak hands in warm water to soften cuticles — then dry completely before polish
7. Remove shine from the nail surface before applying press-ons
8. Use white nail polish as a base coat for any bright colour
9. Apply thin layer of rubbing alcohol to the nail immediately before base coat
10. Push back cuticles after soaking, never dry
11. Shape nails before polish, never after
12. Let any oils (hand cream, cuticle oil) fully absorb before starting — minimum 30 minutes

**H2-3: APPLICATION HACKS (13–24)**
